TY  - JOUR
TI  - Too-Systemic-to-Fail: What Option Markets Imply about Sector-Wide Government Guarantees
AU  - Kelly, Bryan
AU  - Lustig, Hanno
AU  - Van Nieuwerburgh, Stijn
AB  - [We examine the pricing of financial crash insurance during the 2007-2009 financial crisis in US option markets, and we show that a large amount of aggregate tail risk is missing from the cost of financial sector crash insurance during the crisis. The difference in costs between out-of-the-money put options for individual banks and puts on the financial sector index increases four-fold from its precrisis 2003-2007 level. We provide evidence that a collective government guarantee for the financial sector lowers index put prices far more than those of individual banks and explains the increase in the basket-index put spread.]
C1  - Full publication date: JUNE 2016
